<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="616" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="21.[1441,2650,1439,2222]" pageId="21" pageNumber="616">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1443,1793,2031,2064]" pageId="21" pageNumber="616">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Vulnerable on The IUCN Red List. The Senkaku Mole is only known from one location on Uotsurijima Island, which has an area of only 3-8 km?. Overgrazing by domestic goats (Capra hircus) introduced in 1978 has no doubt affected vegetation and ecosystem dynamics on this island.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
